observations.recommendation:
a. The Inventory Committee headed by the Municipal Treasurer’s Office conduct the physical count of its Local Road Network and prepare the Report on Physical Count Local Road Network (RPCLRN). Make use of the template provided in Annex C of COA Circular No. 2015-008 or Appendix 63 of the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs and complete the necessary information in every field. Submit the accomplished RPCLRN to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the books. Also prepare the Road Network Property Card for each Local Road Network;
b. The Municipal Engineer provide cost segregation of every road networks owned by the Municipality per road component for the prior and succeeding years. Submit the road networks duly segregated per road component to the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer. Likewise, provide technical assistance to the inventory committee in the conduct of physical count of its Local Road Networks; and
c. The Municipal Accountant provide the necessary Road Network Ledger Cards and have it reconciled with the balance in the Financial Statements. As to the identified Road Network projects, coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to provide individual cost per road component to be the basis in the computation of depreciation expenses.
